---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of service"
  description="Praxnote's terms of service. The binding agreement is your signed service agreement; this page is a summary."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Terms of service"
    lede="This page summarizes the terms governing use of the Praxnote marketing site. Use of the Praxnote platform is governed by the service agreement and BAA you sign at onboarding."
  />

  <section class="legal-body">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p class="muted">Last updated: 2026-04-30.</p>

      <h2>Use of the marketing site</h2>
      <p>
        praxnote.com is provided for informational purposes. Forms on this site (demo
        requests, contact, BAA requests) initiate a business conversation but do not
        themselves create a customer relationship.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        Don't attempt to disrupt the site, scrape it at high volumes, or attempt to access
        non-public surfaces without authorization. Security disclosures are welcome and
        should be directed to <a href="mailto:security@praxnote.com">security@praxnote.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Trademark and content</h2>
      <p>
        "Praxnote" and the Praxnote logo are property of the Praxnote owners. Content on
        this site (other than third-party material clearly attributed) is owned by Praxnote
        and may not be reproduced without permission, except in accordance with normal
        web-citation practice.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        Praxnote is software for clinical documentation and practice management. It is not
        a clinician. It does not provide clinical advice. Drafts produced by AI features
        are not finished documents. Every clinical artifact in Praxnote is signed by a
        licensed professional before it enters the chart of record.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        In no event shall Praxnote be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
        consequential, or punitive damages arising from use of this marketing site. The
        platform's liability is governed by your signed service agreement.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms; the "last updated" date will reflect the change. Material
        changes affecting active customers are communicated via email under the service
        agreement.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms should go to
        <a href="mailto:legal@praxnote.com">legal@praxnote.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-body { padding: 0 0 clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem); }
  .legal-body h2 { margin: 2rem 0 0.85rem; font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.2vw, 1.7rem); }
  .legal-body p { color: var(--stone-700); line-height: 1.7; max-width: 720px; }
</style>
